{"lemma":"صَقْرَيْ","slug":"صَقْرَيْ","root":"ص.ق.ر","root_slug":"ص-ق-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ق-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24565","n24573","n24574"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"falcon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hawks","tags":["in-plural"],"examples":[{"text":"الصقور","english":"the hawks"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Uncertain with possible connections:\n* The root ص ق ر (ṣ q r) meaning \"to rise high in elevation or temperature\", \"to boil or build up\"; possibly derived onomatopoeically from a bird-of-prey's screeching cry or the screech of steam escaping. Related to Akkadian 𒁲 𒊑 (zaqāru, literally “to build high”); for more see ziggurat.\n* Distantly related to Egyptian z:k:r-A40 (zkr, “Sakar”) an important hawk-headed god of Saqqara, the main funerary site of the Ancient Egyptian capital Memphis. Itself being derived from varying etymologies; perhaps ultimately from a Proto-Afroasiatic root."},"ipa":["/sˤaqr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24565","headword_ar":"صَقَرَ","root":"Sqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) stones, (S,) or a stone, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAquwr","text_ar":"صَاقُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqarahu biAlEaSaA","text_ar":"صَقَرَهُ بِالعَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suqira bihi AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"صُقِرَ بِهِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was thrown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast, upon the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ground was struck with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K. [In some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sqr","text_ar":"صقر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance and the verb explaining it ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drb","text_ar":"ضرب"},{"kind":"text","text":") are in the act. form, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlArD","text_ar":"الارض"},{"kind":"text","text":"is therefore in the accus. case.]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqara Aln~aAra","text_ar":"صَقَرَ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n. as above; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sq~rhA","text_ar":"صقّرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoqiyrN","text_ar":"تَصْقِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kindled, the fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to burn, burn up, burn brightly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fiercely, blaze,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flame."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqaratohu Al$~amosu","text_ar":"صَقَرَتْهُ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun hurt him by its heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pained his brain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell vehemently, with fierce heat, upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was hot upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) [See also 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sqr","text_ar":"سقر"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqaraniY","text_ar":"صَقَرَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikalaAmihi","text_ar":"بِكَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cursed me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calumniated me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. [These meanings seem to be there indicated by the context.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqara All~abanu","text_ar":"صَقَرَ اللَّبَنُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milk was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, intensely sour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASqr~","text_ar":"اصقرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiSoqiraArN","text_ar":"اِصْقِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Samoqara","text_ar":"صَمْقَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Smqr","text_ar":"صمقر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiSomaqar~a","text_ar":"اِصْمَقَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in that art and in the present art. also.) ―         -b2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below, last explanation but one.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n24573","headword_ar":"صَقْرٌ","root":"Sqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hawk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird with which one hunts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"catches, game;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever preys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hunts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"catches game, of the birds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buziAp","text_ar":"بُزِاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAzK","text_ar":"بَازٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAhiyn","text_ar":"شَوَاهِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhiyn","text_ar":"شَاهِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of bird including the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAziY","text_ar":"بَازِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhiyn","text_ar":"شَاهِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zur~aq","text_ar":"زُرَّق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^oyuw^","text_ar":"يُوْيُو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baA$aq","text_ar":"بَاشَق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHát, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$q","text_ar":"بشق"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [like our term “ saker, ” and the French “ sacre, ” &c:] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoqurN","text_ar":"اَصْقُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuquwrN","text_ar":"صُقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuquwrapN","text_ar":"صُقُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiqaArN","text_ar":"صِقَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiqaArapN","text_ar":"صِقَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuqurN","text_ar":"صُقُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) the last of which is said by Th to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuquwrN","text_ar":"صُقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but [ISd says] I hold it to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the fem. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorapN","text_ar":"صَقْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  [And accord. to Reiske, as mentioned by Freytag,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A liberal man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a noble man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as likened to a hawk.]       -A2-  Also, (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorapN","text_ar":"صَقْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of the stroke of the sun,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fierceness of its heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence of its stroke upon the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl. [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqaraAtN","text_ar":"صَقَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A.)       -A3-  Also the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sour milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [and] so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorapN","text_ar":"صَقْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk rendered sour by a stroke of the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk sour in the utmost degree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very sour milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorapN","text_ar":"صَقْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or this latter is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk that has curdled, and of which the thick part has become separate, and the whey become clear, and that has become sour, so as to be a good kind of sauce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazowiY Alwajoha","text_ar":"تَزْوِى الوَجْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='anaA biSaqorapK","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنَا بِصَقْرَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought us some sour milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very sour milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as contracts the face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makes it to wrinkle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biSarobapK","text_ar":"بِصَرْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, A, L.) ―         -b2-  Also, (T, S, M, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorapN","text_ar":"صَقْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exuded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed, juice called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibos","text_ar":"دِبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) in the dial. of the people of El-Medeeneh: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibos","text_ar":"دِبْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fresh ripe dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it is cooked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what flows from them, like honey, and what, when it is cooked, is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~","text_ar":"رُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the honey of fresh ripe dates and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of raisins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqarN","text_ar":"صَقَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honey of fresh ripe dates when it has become dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what exudes from grapes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from raisins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from dates, without their being pressed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqarN","text_ar":"صَقَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or, in the dial. of the Bahránees, [or people of El-Bahreyn,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crude"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibos","text_ar":"دِبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling honey, which flows from baskets of dates when they"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the dates]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are deposited and congested, in an uncovered chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot muSar~aH","text_ar":"بَيْت مُصَرَّح"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the meaning of the epithet is not clear,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with green earthen pots beneath them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AM, TA.) ―         -b3-  And the former, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that has become altered for the worse in taste and colour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, O, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSaq~arN","text_ar":"مُصَقَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqarapN","text_ar":"صَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqoro","text_ar":"صَقْرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^irap","text_ar":"دَايِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of the hair naturally curled"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frizzled in a spiral manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"otherwise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind the place of the liver"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the right"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the back of a horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, TA:) there are two such feathers, (AO, K, TA,) which are the limit of the back. (AO, TA.)       -A5-  Also, [probably as an inf. n., of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saqara","text_ar":"صَقَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting the part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performing the office, of a pimp to"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1706},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men's"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women under covert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M, O, K. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHarami","text_ar":"الحَرَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHurami","text_ar":"الحُرَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Hence the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saq~aAr","text_ar":"صَقَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as some explain it,] occurring in a trad. [which see below]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cursing of such as is not deserving"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuquwrN","text_ar":"صُقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiqaArN","text_ar":"صِقَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","A","S","Sh","As","T","Msb","Mgh","TA","AO"]},{"entry_id":"n24574","headword_ar":"صَقَرُ","root":"Sqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hell;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaru","text_ar":"سَقَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqarN","text_ar":"صَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fallen leaves of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of trees called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofuT","text_ar":"عُرْفُط"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salam","text_ar":"سَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloH","text_ar":"طَلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samur","text_ar":"سَمُر"},{"kind":"text","text":": not so called until they fall. (M.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaqorN","text_ar":"صَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]}}